[SN]TITLE[SN]
Eric Morecambe's Jensen Interceptor for sale at £150,000

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A sports car bought by comedian Eric Morecambe for £4,500 has been put up for sale for £150,000.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Morecambe purchased the Jensen Interceptor in 1968 and kept it in a garage at his home. It was eventually sold to an auction house in 2014.
Buyer Silverstone Auctions contracted Jensen specialists Cropredy Bridge to restore the car's engine, brakes and bodywork.
Morecambe, who died in 1984, was the car's sole owner.
It left Jensen's factory in West Bromwich on 23 September 1968.
